&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Care of the Elderly Consultant salary range £79,860 - £107,668&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Realising your potential with Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is one of a number of opportunities within our hospitals and our partner hospitals as we transition into a ‘Group’ hospital model. Our focus is around expanding our services, to serve our thriving and vibrant community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may wish to further develop your clinical career with a specialist interest, or aspire to be a Clinical Leader or Educator to lead innovative services, and expand the training we offer to our trainees into the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our trainees, are appointed through the new Chelmsford based Anglia Ruskin Medical School, and consistently rate their training experience with us as being excellent to very good.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interested applicants are invited in the first instance to contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Yoganathan Suthahar, email yoganathan.suthahar@meht.nhs.uk (Departmental Clinical Deputy) telephone 01245 514670 for an informal discussion about the job description for this post, which is currently under review.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may wish to explore what could be available to you to advance your potential within this role, or to arrange an informal social visit to enjoy our location and to meet our dedicated, professional and diverse colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location, with a relocation policy package&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chelmsford is set within picturesque ‘Constable’ countryside. With a variety of places to explore, sites to see, plenty of shopping experiences, great restaurants and theatre, as well as the home to ‘Essex cricket club’ there really is something for everyone!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2018, the ‘Times’ voted Chelmsford as best place to live in the UK, regional winner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our hospital has an outstanding nursery. We are also spoilt for choice with excellent schools, housing and transport links. Central London is a 25 minute train ride, Stansted airport 30 minutes away, and the beach 20 miles away.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Further information on our location can be found at: the visit Essex website and the government website by searching for Chelmsford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Yoganathan SuthaharJob titleConsultant GeriatricianEmail addressYoganathan.Suthahar@meht.nhs.ukTelephone number012545 514670Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Yoganathan Suthahar, email yoganathan.suthahar@meht.nhs.uk (Consultant Geriatrician) telephone 01245 514670&lt;/p&gt;
